36#include "krb5_locl.h"

38/* this is an attempt at one of the most horrible `compression'
39 schemes that has ever been invented; it's so amazingly brain-dead
40 that words can not describe it, and all this just to save a few
41 silly bytes */
42
43struct tr_realm {
44 char *realm;
45 unsigned leading_space:1;
46 unsigned leading_slash:1;
47 unsigned trailing_dot:1;
48 struct tr_realm *next;
49};
50
51static void
52free_realms(struct tr_realm *r)
53{
54 struct tr_realm *p;
55 while(r){
56 p = r;
57 r = r->next;
58 free(p->realm);
59 free(p);
60 }
61}
62
63static int
64make_path(krb5_context context, struct tr_realm *r,
65 const char *from, const char *to)
66{
67 struct tr_realm *tmp;
68 const char *p;
69
70 if(strlen(from) < strlen(to)){
71 const char *str;
72 str = from;
73 from = to;
74 to = str;
75 }
76
77 if(strcmp(from + strlen(from) - strlen(to), to) == 0){
78 p = from;
79 while(1){
80 p = strchr(p, '.');
81 if(p == NULL) {
82 krb5_clear_error_message (context);
83 return KRB5KDC_ERR_POLICY;
84 }
85 p++;
86 if(strcmp(p, to) == 0)
87 break;
88 tmp = calloc(1, sizeof(*tmp));
89 if(tmp == NULL)
90 return krb5_enomem(context);
91 tmp->next = r->next;
92 r->next = tmp;
93 tmp->realm = strdup(p);
94 if(tmp->realm == NULL){
95 r->next = tmp->next;
96 free(tmp);
97 return krb5_enomem(context);
98 }
99 }
100 }else if(strncmp(from, to, strlen(to)) == 0){
101 p = from + strlen(from);
102 while(1){
103 while(p >= from && *p != '/') p--;
104 if(p == from)
105 return KRB5KDC_ERR_POLICY;
106
107 if(strncmp(to, from, p - from) == 0)
108 break;
109 tmp = calloc(1, sizeof(*tmp));
110 if(tmp == NULL)
111 return krb5_enomem(context);
112 tmp->next = r->next;
113 r->next = tmp;
114 tmp->realm = malloc(p - from + 1);
115 if(tmp->realm == NULL){
116 r->next = tmp->next;
117 free(tmp);
118 return krb5_enomem(context);
119 }
120 memcpy(tmp->realm, from, p - from);
121 tmp->realm[p - from] = '\0';
122 p--;
123 }
124 } else {
125 krb5_clear_error_message (context);
126 return KRB5KDC_ERR_POLICY;
127 }
128
129 return 0;
130}
131
132static int
133make_paths(krb5_context context,
134 struct tr_realm *realms, const char *client_realm,
135 const char *server_realm)
136{
137 struct tr_realm *r;
138 int ret;
139 const char *prev_realm = client_realm;
140 const char *next_realm = NULL;
141 for(r = realms; r; r = r->next){
142 /* it *might* be that you can have more than one empty
143 component in a row, at least that's how I interpret the
144 "," exception in 1510 */
145 if(r->realm[0] == '\0'){
146 while(r->next && r->next->realm[0] == '\0')
147 r = r->next;
148 if(r->next)
149 next_realm = r->next->realm;
150 else
151 next_realm = server_realm;
152 ret = make_path(context, r, prev_realm, next_realm);
153 if(ret){
154 free_realms(realms);
155 return ret;
156 }
157 }
158 prev_realm = r->realm;
159 }
160 return 0;
161}
162
163static int
164expand_realms(krb5_context context,
165 struct tr_realm *realms, const char *client_realm)
166{
167 struct tr_realm *r;
168 const char *prev_realm = NULL;
169 for(r = realms; r; r = r->next){
170 if(r->trailing_dot){
171 char *tmp;
172 size_t len;
173
174 if(prev_realm == NULL)
175 prev_realm = client_realm;
176
177 len = strlen(r->realm) + strlen(prev_realm) + 1;
178
179 tmp = realloc(r->realm, len);
180 if(tmp == NULL){
181 free_realms(realms);
182 return krb5_enomem(context);
183 }
184 r->realm = tmp;
185 strlcat(r->realm, prev_realm, len);
186 }else if(r->leading_slash && !r->leading_space && prev_realm){
187 /* yet another exception: if you use x500-names, the
188 leading realm doesn't have to be "quoted" with a space */
189 char *tmp;
190 size_t len = strlen(r->realm) + strlen(prev_realm) + 1;
191
192 tmp = malloc(len);
193 if(tmp == NULL){
194 free_realms(realms);
195 return krb5_enomem(context);
196 }
197 strlcpy(tmp, prev_realm, len);
198 strlcat(tmp, r->realm, len);
199 free(r->realm);
200 r->realm = tmp;
201 }
202 prev_realm = r->realm;
203 }
204 return 0;
205}
206
207static struct tr_realm *
208make_realm(char *realm)
209{
210 struct tr_realm *r;
211 char *p, *q;
212 int quote = 0;
213 r = calloc(1, sizeof(*r));
214 if(r == NULL){
215 free(realm);
216 return NULL;
217 }
218 r->realm = realm;
219 for(p = q = r->realm; *p; p++){
220 if(p == r->realm && *p == ' '){
221 r->leading_space = 1;
222 continue;
223 }
224 if(q == r->realm && *p == '/')
225 r->leading_slash = 1;
226 if(quote){
227 *q++ = *p;
228 quote = 0;
229 continue;
230 }
231 if(*p == '\\'){
232 quote = 1;
233 continue;
234 }
235 if(p[0] == '.' && p[1] == '\0')
236 r->trailing_dot = 1;
237 *q++ = *p;
238 }
239 *q = '\0';
240 return r;
241}
242
243static struct tr_realm*
244append_realm(struct tr_realm *head, struct tr_realm *r)
245{
246 struct tr_realm *p;
247 if(head == NULL){
248 r->next = NULL;
249 return r;
250 }
251 p = head;
252 while(p->next) p = p->next;
253 p->next = r;
254 return head;
255}
256
257static int
258decode_realms(krb5_context context,
259 const char *tr, int length, struct tr_realm **realms)
260{
261 struct tr_realm *r = NULL;
262
263 char *tmp;
264 int quote = 0;
265 const char *start = tr;
266 int i;
267
268 for(i = 0; i < length; i++){
269 if(quote){
270 quote = 0;
271 continue;
272 }
273 if(tr[i] == '\\'){
274 quote = 1;
275 continue;
276 }
277 if(tr[i] == ','){
278 tmp = malloc(tr + i - start + 1);
279 if(tmp == NULL)
280 return krb5_enomem(context);
281 memcpy(tmp, start, tr + i - start);
282 tmp[tr + i - start] = '\0';
283 r = make_realm(tmp);
284 if(r == NULL){
285 free_realms(*realms);
286 return krb5_enomem(context);
287 }
288 *realms = append_realm(*realms, r);
289 start = tr + i + 1;
290 }
291 }
292 tmp = malloc(tr + i - start + 1);
293 if(tmp == NULL){
294 free(*realms);
295 return krb5_enomem(context);
296 }
297 memcpy(tmp, start, tr + i - start);
298 tmp[tr + i - start] = '\0';
299 r = make_realm(tmp);
300 if(r == NULL){
301 free_realms(*realms);
302 return krb5_enomem(context);
303 }
304 *realms = append_realm(*realms, r);
305
306 return 0;
307}

310KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
311krb5_domain_x500_decode(krb5_context context,
312 krb5_data tr, char ***realms, unsigned int *num_realms,
313 const char *client_realm, const char *server_realm)
314{
315 struct tr_realm *r = NULL;
316 struct tr_realm *p, **q;
317 int ret;
318
319 if(tr.length == 0) {
320 *realms = NULL;
321 *num_realms = 0;
322 return 0;
323 }
324
325 /* split string in components */
326 ret = decode_realms(context, tr.data, tr.length, &r);
327 if(ret)
328 return ret;
329
330 /* apply prefix rule */
331 ret = expand_realms(context, r, client_realm);
332 if(ret)
333 return ret;
334
335 ret = make_paths(context, r, client_realm, server_realm);
336 if(ret)
337 return ret;
338
339 /* remove empty components and count realms */
340 *num_realms = 0;
341 for(q = &r; *q; ){
342 if((*q)->realm[0] == '\0'){
343 p = *q;
344 *q = (*q)->next;
345 free(p->realm);
346 free(p);
347 }else{
348 q = &(*q)->next;
349 (*num_realms)++;
350 }
351 }
352 if (*num_realms + 1 > UINT_MAX/sizeof(**realms))
353 return ERANGE;
354
355 {
356 char **R;
357 R = malloc((*num_realms + 1) * sizeof(*R));
358 if (R == NULL)
359 return krb5_enomem(context);
360 *realms = R;
361 while(r){
362 *R++ = r->realm;
363 p = r->next;
364 free(r);
365 r = p;
366 }
367 }
368 return 0;
369}

371KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
372krb5_domain_x500_encode(char **realms, unsigned int num_realms,
373 krb5_data *encoding)
374{
375 char *s = NULL;
376 int len = 0;
377 unsigned int i;
378 krb5_data_zero(encoding);
379 if (num_realms == 0)
380 return 0;
381 for(i = 0; i < num_realms; i++){
382 len += strlen(realms[i]);
383 if(realms[i][0] == '/')
384 len++;
385 }
386 len += num_realms - 1;
387 s = malloc(len + 1);
388 if (s == NULL)
389 return ENOMEM;
390 *s = '\0';
391 for(i = 0; i < num_realms; i++){
392 if(i)
393 strlcat(s, ",", len + 1);
394 if(realms[i][0] == '/')
395 strlcat(s, " ", len + 1);
396 strlcat(s, realms[i], len + 1);
397 }
398 encoding->data = s;
399 encoding->length = strlen(s);
400 return 0;
401}

403KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION void KRB5_LIB_CALL
404_krb5_free_capath(krb5_context context, char **capath)
405{
406 char **s;
407
408 for (s = capath; s && *s; ++s)
409 free(*s);
410 free(capath);
411}

413struct hier_iter {
414 const char *local_realm;
415 const char *server_realm;
416 const char *lr; /* Pointer into tail of local realm */
417 const char *sr; /* Pointer into tail of server realm */
418 size_t llen; /* Length of local_realm */
419 size_t slen; /* Length of server_realm */
420 size_t len; /* Length of common suffix */
421 size_t num; /* Path element count */
422};
423
424/*
425 * Step up from local_realm to common suffix, or else down to server_realm.
426 */
427static const char *
428hier_next(struct hier_iter *state)
429{
430 const char *lr = state->lr;
431 const char *sr = state->sr;
432 const char *lsuffix = state->local_realm + state->llen - state->len;
433 const char *server_realm = state->server_realm;
434
435 if (lr != NULL) {
436 while (lr < lsuffix)
437 if (*lr++ == '.')
438 return state->lr = lr;
439 state->lr = NULL;
440 }
441 if (sr != NULL) {
442 while (--sr >= server_realm)
443 if (sr == server_realm || sr[-1] == '.')
444 return state->sr = sr;
445 state->sr = NULL;
446 }
447 return NULL;
448}
449
450static void
451hier_init(struct hier_iter *state, const char *local_realm, const char *server_realm)
452{
453 size_t llen;
454 size_t slen;
455 size_t len = 0;
456 const char *lr;
457 const char *sr;
458
459 state->local_realm = local_realm;
460 state->server_realm = server_realm;
461 state->llen = llen = strlen(local_realm);
462 state->slen = slen = strlen(server_realm);
463 state->len = 0;
464 state->num = 0;
465
466 if (slen == 0 || llen == 0)
467 return;
468
469 /* Find first difference from the back */
470 for (lr = local_realm + llen, sr = server_realm + slen;
471 lr != local_realm && sr != server_realm;
472 --lr, --sr) {
473 if (lr[-1] != sr[-1])
474 break;
475 if (lr[-1] == '.')
476 len = llen - (lr - local_realm);
477 }
478
479 /* Nothing in common? */
480 if (*lr == '\0')
481 return;
482
483 /* Everything in common? */
484 if (llen == slen && lr == local_realm)
485 return;
486
487 /* Is one realm is a suffix of the other? */
488 if ((llen < slen && lr == local_realm && sr[-1] == '.') ||
489 (llen > slen && sr == server_realm && lr[-1] == '.'))
490 len = llen - (lr - local_realm);
491
492 state->len = len;
493 /* `lr` starts at local realm and walks up the tree to common suffix */
494 state->lr = local_realm;
495 /* `sr` starts at common suffix in server realm and walks down the tree */
496 state->sr = server_realm + slen - len;
497
498 /* Count elements and reset */
499 while (hier_next(state) != NULL)
500 ++state->num;
501 state->lr = local_realm;
502 state->sr = server_realm + slen - len;
503}
504
505/*
506 * Find a referral path from client_realm to server_realm via local_realm.
507 * Either via [capaths] or hierarchicaly.
508 */
509KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
510_krb5_find_capath(krb5_context context,
511 const char *client_realm,
512 const char *local_realm,
513 const char *server_realm,
514 krb5_boolean use_hierarchical,
515 char ***rpath,
516 size_t *npath)
517{
518 char **confpath;
519 char **capath;
520 struct hier_iter hier_state;
521 char **rp;
522 const char *r;
523
524 *rpath = NULL;
525 *npath = 0;
526
527 confpath = krb5_config_get_strings(context, NULL, "capaths",
528 client_realm, server_realm, NULL);
529 if (confpath == NULL)
530 confpath = krb5_config_get_strings(context, NULL, "capaths",
531 local_realm, server_realm, NULL);
532 /*
533 * With a [capaths] setting from the client to the server we look for our
534 * own realm in the list. If our own realm is not present, we return the
535 * full list. Otherwise, we return our realm's successors, or possibly
536 * NULL. Ignoring a [capaths] settings risks loops plus would violate
537 * explicit policy and the principle of least surpise.
538 */
539 if (confpath != NULL) {
540 char **start = confpath;
541 size_t i;
542 size_t n;
543
544 for (rp = start; *rp; rp++)
545 if (strcmp(*rp, local_realm) == 0)
546 start = rp+1;
547 n = rp - start;
548
549 if (n == 0) {
550 krb5_config_free_strings(confpath);
551 return 0;
552 }
553
554 capath = calloc(n + 1, sizeof(*capath));
555 if (capath == NULL) {
556 krb5_config_free_strings(confpath);
557 return krb5_enomem(context);
558 }
559
560 for (i = 0, rp = start; *rp; rp++) {
561 if ((capath[i++] = strdup(*rp)) == NULL) {
562 _krb5_free_capath(context, capath);
563 krb5_config_free_strings(confpath);
564 return krb5_enomem(context);
565 }
566 }
567 krb5_config_free_strings(confpath);
568 capath[i] = NULL;
569 *rpath = capath;
570 *npath = n;
571 return 0;
572 }
573
574 /* The use_hierarchical flag makes hierarchical path lookup unconditional */
575 if (! use_hierarchical &&
576 ! krb5_config_get_bool_default(context, NULL, TRUE, "libdefaults",
577 "allow_hierarchical_capaths", NULL))
578 return 0;
579
580 /*
581 * When validating transit paths, local_realm == client_realm. Otherwise,
582 * with hierarchical referrals, they may differ, and we may be building a
583 * path forward from our own realm!
584 */
585 hier_init(&hier_state, local_realm, server_realm);
586 if (hier_state.num == 0)
587 return 0;
588
589 rp = capath = calloc(hier_state.num + 1, sizeof(*capath));
590 if (capath == NULL)
591 return krb5_enomem(context);
592 while ((r = hier_next(&hier_state)) != NULL) {
593 if ((*rp++ = strdup(r)) == NULL) {
594 _krb5_free_capath(context, capath);
595 return krb5_enomem(context);
596 }
597 }
598
599 *rp = NULL;
600 *rpath = capath;
601 *npath = hier_state.num;
602 return 0;
603}

605KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
606krb5_check_transited(krb5_context context,
607 krb5_const_realm client_realm,
608 krb5_const_realm server_realm,
609 krb5_realm *realms,
610 unsigned int num_realms,
611 int *bad_realm)
612{
613 krb5_error_code ret = 0;
614 char **capath = NULL;
615 size_t num_capath = 0;
616 size_t i = 0;
617 size_t j = 0;
618
619 /* In transit checks hierarchical capaths are optional */
620 ret = _krb5_find_capath(context, client_realm, client_realm, server_realm,
621 FALSE, &capath, &num_capath);
622 if (ret)
623 return ret;
624
625 for (i = 0; i < num_realms; i++) {
626 for (j = 0; j < num_capath; ++j) {
627 if (strcmp(realms[i], capath[j]) == 0)
628 break;
629 }
630 if (j == num_capath) {
631 _krb5_free_capath(context, capath);
632 krb5_set_error_message (context, KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_ILL_CR_TKT,
633 N_("no transit allowed "
634 "through realm %s from %s to %s", ""),
635 realms[i], client_realm, server_realm);
636 if (bad_realm)
637 *bad_realm = i;
638 return KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_ILL_CR_TKT;
639 }
640 }
641
642 _krb5_free_capath(context, capath);
643 return 0;
644}
645
646KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
647krb5_check_transited_realms(krb5_context context,
648 const char *const *realms,
649 unsigned int num_realms,
650 int *bad_realm)
651{
652 size_t i;
653 int ret = 0;
654 char **bad_realms = krb5_config_get_strings(context, NULL,
655 "libdefaults",
656 "transited_realms_reject",
657 NULL);
658 if(bad_realms == NULL)
659 return 0;
660
661 for(i = 0; i < num_realms; i++) {
662 char **p;
663 for(p = bad_realms; *p; p++)
664 if(strcmp(*p, realms[i]) == 0) {
665 ret = KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_ILL_CR_TKT;
666 krb5_set_error_message (context, ret,
667 N_("no transit allowed "
668 "through realm %s", ""),
669 *p);
670 if(bad_realm)
671 *bad_realm = i;
672 break;
673 }
674 }
675 krb5_config_free_strings(bad_realms);
676 return ret;
677}
